that's a great question.

00:04:08.698 --> 00:04:11.716
So, natural selection,
often people talk about it

00:04:11.716 --> 00:04:15.613
as sort of, having three key ingredients.

00:04:15.613 --> 00:04:18.495
To see how it works, let's
imagine that we're just looking

00:04:18.495 --> 00:04:20.775
at a population of beetles.

00:04:20.775 --> 00:04:24.192
So picture you're beetles, to start with.

00:04:25.768 --> 00:04:29.275
What would we need to have,
in order for these beetles,

00:04:29.275 --> 00:04:32.580
as a group, to evolve
